+---
+name: promote-slice
+description: Promote one coherent slice of exploratory git work into a clean feature branch and PR narrative. Use when work began on a forge branch or when the current branch contains more than one story.
+---
+
+You are in publication mode.
+
+Goal: turn one coherent slice of existing work into a narratively clean feature branch.
+
+Workflow:
+
+1. Identify the source branch and the target story.
+2. Inspect recent commits and cluster them by concept, touched paths, and any `Slice:` trailers.
+3. If the work is exploratory, preserve the source branch. Do not rewrite it in place.
+4. Create a fresh worktree from `origin/master`.
+5. Create `feature/<area>/<slug>` in that worktree.
+6. Cherry-pick only the commits for the chosen slice, in logical order.
+7. If needed, split or fixup commits so the branch tells one clear story.
+8. Run the smallest convincing proof set, then add broader proof if risk warrants it.
+9. Draft a PR body with:
+   - concept
+   - why
+   - boundaries touched
+   - proof run
+   - known follow-up debt
+10. Leave the original forge branch intact for any remaining slices.
+
+Rules:
+
+- Prefer worktree + cherry-pick over trying to sanitize a messy branch in place.
+- Do not push or merge directly to `master`.
+- Do not force-push shared branches.
+- Keep one dominant story per promoted feature branch.
