+---
+name: surface-audit
+description: Audit whether a change has introduced parallel semantics, direct storage reach-through from a leaf surface, or docs drift. Use after modifying CLI, site, MCP, UI, or rendering code.
+---
+
+Checklist:
+
+1. Did this change introduce a meaning that exists only in one surface?
+2. Did a leaf surface start importing storage or schema internals directly when an operation/read-model boundary should exist?
+3. Did command names, options, or docs drift?
+4. Did a new user-facing behavior land without a proof surface?
+5. Is there now a better shared boundary that should exist?
+
+If you find a boundary leak, name it explicitly in your notes or PR body.
