+# Storage guidance
+
+This package owns canonical persisted meaning and durable read-side materialization.
+
+- Prefer schemas, repositories, and materializers that can be consumed by many surfaces.
+- Avoid adding surface-specific row shapes or ad-hoc queries when operations or read models can own them.
+- New derived tables should come with explicit status, provenance/version expectations, and a repair story.
+- Think in terms of storage contracts, not just helper functions.
